In digital marketing, a conversion is an action taken by a user that is considered valuable to your business. This could be anything from making a purchase, signing up for a newsletter, downloading an app, or filling out a contact form. Essentially, it's any desired action that you want users to take on your website or app.
Why is there so much delayed traffic?

There could be several reasons for delayed traffic to your ads or website. It might be due to server issues, network latency, or even the time it takes for ad platforms to process and display your ads. If you're experiencing significant delays, it might be helpful to check with your hosting provider or the ad platform you're using for any known issues or maintenance activities.

Fake traffic, also known as bot traffic, can occur for various reasons. It might be due to automated scripts or bots that are designed to mimic real user behavior. This can happen if your ads or website are targeted by malicious actors or if there are issues with the ad platform's traffic quality. To address this, you can use tools and services that help detect and filter out fake traffic, and report any suspicious activity to the ad platform you're using.
